-- Russia Harvested Almost 1 Million Tons of Grains for Next Season
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2012-06-27T15:41:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-27/russia-harvested-almost-1-million-tons-of-grains-for-next-season.html
Russia , the world’s third
biggest  wheat exporter , has harvested almost 1 million metric
tons of grain for the 2012-13 marketing year.  Average yields were 2.8 tons a hectare (2.47 acres), down
from 4.8 tons a year earlier, the ministry said in a  statement 
on its website today. The marketing year starts July 1.  The wheat crop will be 49 million to 50 million tons for
2012-13, Dmitry Bobkov, the  Agriculture Ministry ’s spokesman,
said yesterday. The current season’s wheat production is 56.2
million tons, according to state statistics data.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
